4. THIRD-PARTY SERVICES (CRITICAL)
----------------------------------

The Software talks to independent temporary-email and related services
operated by third parties (websites, APIs, unofficial endpoints, etc.).
Those parties are not affiliated with, endorsed by, controlled by, or
guaranteed by the authors of this Software.

You understand and accept that:

  a) Each provider has its own Terms of Service, Acceptable Use Policy,
     Privacy Policy, rate limits, authentication rules, and geographic
     restrictions. You must read and comply with them yourself.

  b) Providers may change, throttle, captcha-gate, block, or shut down
     endpoints at any time without notice. The Software may break as a
     result. That is expected risk, not a defect you can claim damages for.

  c) Some integrations use undocumented or unofficial HTTP surfaces that
     mirror a website. Those are inherently fragile and may violate a
     provider's terms. Using them is entirely your choice and risk.

  d) Official paid APIs (where supported) still require your own API keys,
     accounts, billing, and compliance with that vendor's contract.

  e) The authors do not operate mail servers for you, do not store your
     mail, and cannot recover lost messages or addresses.


5. NO SENSITIVE USE
-------------------

Temporary / disposable mailboxes are often public, shared, short-lived,
guessable, or logged by the provider.

DO NOT use this Software or any address it creates for:

  • banking, payments, crypto, or financial accounts
  • government, healthcare, legal, or employment identity
  • primary personal email or long-term account recovery
  • passwords, 2FA backup codes, private keys, or secrets
  • anything you would not want a stranger to read

If you do anyway, that is solely your responsibility.


6. LAWFUL AND ETHICAL USE ONLY
------------------------------

You agree not to use the Software to:

  • violate any law, regulation, or third-party right
  • commit fraud, identity theft, impersonation, or phishing
  • evade sanctions, age gates, or legally required identity checks where
    doing so is unlawful
  • spam, harass, abuse, or attack any person or system
  • bypass security controls of a service in a way that is illegal or
    clearly prohibited by that service's terms (you remain responsible for
    interpreting those terms)
  • distribute malware or conduct unauthorized access

The Software is intended for legitimate development, testing, privacy
sandboxing, and similar non-abusive purposes. Misuse is on you.


7. AUTOMATION, SCRAPING, AND BOT DETECTION
-----------------------------------------

Automated access may trigger captchas, IP bans, legal notices, or account
termination on third-party sites. The Software may surface errors such as
captcha / bot challenges. That does not create any obligation for the
authors to bypass protections, maintain workarounds, or keep unofficial
endpoints working.

You are responsible for:

  • your network identity (IP, proxies, VPNs)
  • request volume and timing
  • any consequences of automation


8. DATA, PRIVACY, AND SECRETS
-----------------------------

  a) Messages in temporary inboxes may be readable by others who know or
     guess the address, or by the provider itself.

  b) Credentials returned by the Software (tokens, passwords, cookies,
     session ids) are sensitive within the scope of that disposable inbox.
     Protect them in your own environment; the authors never receive them
     unless you deliberately send them somewhere.

  c) API keys you place in environment variables or pass into constructors
     are your secrets. Do not commit them to public repositories.

  d) The Software does not provide a privacy guarantee, encryption
     guarantee, or data-processing agreement.


